# Performance Standards

Performance is a feature. Fast software feels intelligent.

## Avoid

Unnecessary re-renders, duplicate fetches, huge client bundles, blocking work on the main thread, unbounded lists without pagination/virtualization.

## Prefer

- Server Components / server data loading when the stack supports it
- Lazy routes and code splitting for heavy panels
- Pagination or virtualization for large tables
- Image optimization and correct sizes
- Caching and `revalidatePath` / query invalidation with intent
- Debounced search

## Discipline

Do not premature-optimize. Measure bottlenecks. Keep code simple while fixing what users feel.
